cmCourseInfo.description: This course explores key issues in Indigenous politics in Canada. Provides students with an overview of historical and contemporary socio-political issues in Indigenous societies and institutions such as Indigenous self-governance, land claims and treaty negotiations.
cmCourseInfo.title: Indigenous Politics in Canada
cmCourseInfo.prerequisitesText: 4.0 credits, or 1.0 credit in POL/ JPA/ JPF/ JPI/ JPR/ JPS/ JRA courses, or INS201Y1/ (INS201H1, INS202H1)

notes.name: Course Note
notes.content:
Timetable Instructions

Tutorial Enrolment Instructions: 

  • Tutorial enrolment is mandatory for this course.
  • All students are required to enrol in a tutorial section at the time of course enrolment.
  • Enrol in a section that works with your schedule.

 

Prerequisites/Exclusions:

  • Prerequisites and exclusions are enforced for all POL courses.  Please consult the Faculty of Arts and Science Calendar https://artsci.calendar.utoronto.ca/section/Political-Science, or the POL Undergraduate website https://www.politics.utoronto.ca/undergraduate/curriculum-course-information/current-fallwinter-courses for details.
  • Students will be removed from this course if they do not have the prerequisite as stated in the Faculty of Arts and Science Calendar.

       

Note:

  • If you do have the background preparation to take this course, please contact the instructor for permission to waive the prerequisite before enrolling in the course.
  • If permission is granted by the instructor, please forward the email approval to the Undergraduate Assistant at undergrad.polsci@utoronto.ca.
  • Students who have completed the equivalent course at UTM or UTSC, please reach out to the Undergraduate Assistant at undergrad.polsci@utoronto.ca.
